                    </a>
                    <p class="card-text mb-0">
                        English Reading and Writing classes are taught by Ben Fiedor,
                        who holds a Ph.D. of Philosophy degree from Brown University
                        and has many years of teaching and tutoring experience.
                    </p>

                    <a href="#" class="btn btn-style btn-primary mt-4">Read More</a>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-lg-4 col-md-6 causes-grid align-self-start">
                <div class="causes-grid-info">
                    <a href="#"><img src="~/images/course_chess.jpg" class="img-fuild" alt=""></a>
                    <a href="#" class="cause-title-wrap">
                        <h4 class="cause-title">
                            Chess
                        </h4>
                    </a>
                    <p class="card-text mb-0">
                        Chess classes are taught by Gregory Rogers,
                        the founder and coach of Chess Masters of Delaware.
                        Mr. Rogers has led the students in the club to win many national and regional trophies.
                    </p>

                    <a href="#" class="btn btn-style btn-primary mt-4">Read More</a>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-lg-4 col-md-6 causes-grid align-self-start">
                <div class="causes-grid-info">
                    <a href="#"><img src="~/images/course_drawing.jpg" class="img-fuild" alt=""></a>
                    <a href="#" class="cause-title-wrap">
                        <h4 class="cause-title">
                            Drawing
                        </h4>
                    </a>
                    <p class="card-text mb-0">
                        In our drawing classes, our experienced art teacher guides the students to
                        explore basic drawing principles such as line, color, and texture and
                        develop painting techniques using various paint media.
                    </p>

                    <a href="#" class="btn btn-style btn-primary mt-4">Read More</a>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-lg-4 col-md-6 causes-grid align-self-start">
                <div class="causes-grid-info">
                    <a href="#"><img src="~/images/course_dancing.jpg" class="img-fuild" alt=""></a>
                    <a href="#" class="cause-title-wrap">
                        <h4 class="cause-title">
                            Dancing
                        </h4>
                    </a>
                    <p class="card-text mb-0">
                        Our dance classes teach Chinese Folk Dance and Contemporary dance.
                        Students learn dance and gain valuable performing experience through
                        participation in weekly classes and holiday performances.
                    </p>

                    <a href="#" class="btn btn-style btn-primary mt-4">Read More</a>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-lg-4 col-md-6 causes-grid align-self-start">
                <div class="causes-grid-info">
                    <a href="#"><img src="~/images/course_speaking.jpg" class="img-fuild" alt=""></a>
                    <a href="#" class="cause-title-wrap">
                        <h4 class="cause-title">
                            Public Speaking
                        </h4>
                    </a>
                    <p class="card-text mb-0">
                        Public speaking classes are taught by Mike Nie,
                        founder of “Speak to lead LLC”.
                        Coach Nie has won many awards in public speaking and is a distinguished toastmaster.
                        He has years of experience teaching public speaking.

                        In each meeting, speaking techniques are taught through watching and analyzing famous
                        speeches. After each lesson, students are assigned a 2-3 min speech homework to
                        be presented during class. Homework submission is analyzed individually by
                        the coach both offline and during class.
                    </p>


                    <a href="#" class="btn btn-style btn-primary mt-4">Read More</a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
